<!--
  MangroveWatch — sitemap.xml
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  BEFORE SUBMITTING TO GOOGLE SEARCH CONSOLE
  ───────────────────────────────────────────
  1. Replace every occurrence of https://mangrovewatch.vercel.app with
     your actual verified domain (must match exactly what you add
     in Search Console under "Add Property").

  2. Upload this file to the ROOT of your web server so it is
     reachable at:  https://mangrovewatch.vercel.app/sitemap.xml

  3. In Google Search Console → Sitemaps → enter:  sitemap.xml
     and click "Submit".

  NOTE ON HASH ROUTING
  ─────────────────────
  This site uses hash-based client-side routing (#home, #conservation,
  etc.). Google's crawler does not follow hash fragments as separate
  URLs — it treats the root URL as a single page. The section entries
  below (/#conservation, /#species, …) are included for completeness
  and for any crawlers/bots that do resolve them.

  For full per-section Google indexation in the future, consider
  migrating routing to the History API (pushState paths without #).
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
